  pages        = {1124--1146},
  date         = {2024-12-11},
  abstract     = {Social media creates the possibility for rapid, viral spread
                  of content, but how many posts actually reach millions? And is
                  misinformation special in how it propagates? We answer these
                  questions by analyzing the virality of and exposure to
                  information on Facebook during the U.S. 2020 presidential
                  election. We examine the diffusion trees of the approximately
