                  social context that shape their outcomes. We then offer
                  guidance for improving the science of AI by engaging
                  lived-experience experts in the design, data collection, and
                  interpretation of scientific evaluations. This article reviews
                  common models of public engagement in AI research alongside
                  common concerns about participatory methods, including
                  questions about generalizable knowledge, subjectivity,
